# Comprehensive UX/UI Improvement Plan for iskrib_v3

## Overview

This plan covers four areas: (1) Toast System, (2) Feed & Page Polish, (3) Micro-interactions, and (4) Accessibility & Design Tokens. The phases are ordered by impact-to-effort ratio, with each phase delivering standalone value.

---

## Phase 1: Design Tokens & Toast Foundation (Estimated: 2-3 days)

This phase establishes the infrastructure that all other phases depend on.

### 1A. Design Tokens in `client/src/index.css`

Add to the existing `:root` block (and the `[data-theme="dark"]` block where needed):

**Spacing scale** (4px base grid):
```css
--space-1: 4px;
--space-2: 8px;
--space-3: 12px;
--space-4: 16px;
--space-5: 20px;
--space-6: 24px;
--space-8: 32px;
--space-10: 40px;
--space-12: 48px;
--space-16: 64px;
```

**Type scale tokens**:
```css
--text-xs: 0.7rem;     /* 11.2px - captions, dates */
--text-sm: 0.78rem;    /* 12.5px - card excerpts, counts */
--text-base: 0.875rem; /* 14px - body text */
--text-md: 1rem;       /* 16px - UI elements */
--text-lg: 1.125rem;   /* 18px - subheadings */
--text-xl: 1.5rem;     /* 24px - headings */
--text-2xl: 2rem;      /* 32px - page titles */
--text-3xl: 2.5rem;    /* 40px - hero text */
```

**Animation tokens** (used by phases 2-3):
```css
--ease-out-quart: cubic-bezier(0.25, 1, 0.5, 1);
--ease-spring: cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1);
--duration-fast: 150ms;
--duration-normal: 250ms;
--duration-slow: 400ms;
```

**Focus ring token**:
```css
--focus-ring: 0 0 0 2px var(--bg-primary), 0 0 0 4px var(--accent-amber);
```

**Files to modify:**
- `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\index.css` -- add tokens to both `:root` and `[data-theme="dark"]` blocks

### 1B. Toast System

**New files to create:**

1. **`client/src/components/Toast/ToastContext.jsx`** -- Context + Provider + useToast hook

The provider wraps the app in `main.jsx` (inside `ThemeProvider`, outside `AuthProvider`). State is a queue of toast objects: `{ id, type, message, duration }`.

```jsx
// API shape:
const { toast } = useToast();
toast.success('Post bookmarked');
toast.error('Failed to save. Please try again.');
toast.warning('You are offline');
toast.info('Draft auto-saved');
```

Implementation details:
- Toast queue with max 3 visible at once, FIFO
- Each toast auto-dismisses after `duration` (default 3500ms for success/info, 5000ms for error/warning)
- Dismiss on click or swipe-away
- `id` uses `crypto.randomUUID()` or `Date.now()` fallback

2. **`client/src/components/Toast/Toast.jsx`** -- Individual toast component

Uses Framer Motion `AnimatePresence` for enter/exit. Renders in a portal at document body level.

```jsx
// Enter: slide from right + fade in
// Exit: slide right + fade out
<motion.div
  initial={{ x: 60, opacity: 0 }}
  animate={{ x: 0, opacity: 1 }}
  exit={{ x: 60, opacity: 0 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.25, ease: [0.25, 1, 0.5, 1] }}
>
```

Visual design:
- Positioned bottom-right on desktop (right: 24px, bottom: 24px), bottom-center on mobile
- Glass morphism: `background: var(--bg-glass); backdrop-filter: blur(12px); border: 1px solid var(--bg-glass-border);`
- Left accent stripe per type: success=`var(--color-success)`, error=`var(--color-danger)`, warning=`var(--accent-amber)`, info=`var(--accent-purple)`
- Small icon per type (SVG, inline)
- Font: `var(--font-ui)`, size `var(--text-sm)`
- Shadow: `var(--shadow-dropdown)`
- `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` -- disable slide animation, use simple opacity fade

3. **`client/src/components/Toast/Toast.css`** -- Styles

4. **`client/src/components/Toast/ToastContainer.jsx`** -- Portal wrapper that renders the stacked toast list

**Files to modify:**
- `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\main.jsx` -- wrap with `<ToastProvider>` inside `ThemeProvider`
- `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\postCards\PostCards.jsx` -- replace ad-hoc `bookmarkedMessage` / `showBookmarkedMessage` state + timeout with `toast.success()`. Remove lines 44-45 (state), lines 287-311 (the async bookmark handler's message logic), and the inline toast JSX at the render. Replace with single `toast.success('Post bookmarked')` / `toast.success('Bookmark removed')` call in the handler.
- `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\ContentViewer\ContentView.jsx` -- same pattern, replace inline bookmark message
- `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\utils\useMutation.js` -- add `onError` toast calls to `useBookMarkMutation`, `useLikeMutation`, `useFollowMutation`, `useReactionMutation`, `useRepostMutation`. Each `onError` callback calls `toast.error()`. Since hooks cannot call `useToast` (they are not components), pass an optional `onErrorCallback` parameter OR use a global event emitter pattern. **Recommended approach:** Accept an optional `toastRef` parameter or use the simpler approach of having consumers pass `onError` callbacks when calling `mutate()`.

**Better pattern for mutation error toasts:** Rather than modifying `useMutation.js` hooks, add error handling at the call sites. For example in `PostCards.jsx`:

```jsx
const { toast } = useToast();

const handleReaction = (journalId, receiverId, reactionType) => {
    if(!session) return openAuthModal();
    mutationReaction.mutate(
        { journalId, receiverId, reactionType },
        { onError: () => toast.error('Failed to react. Please try again.') }
    );
};
```

This is cleaner because each call site can provide context-specific error messages.

**Integration points for error toasts:**
- `PostCards.jsx` -- bookmark, reaction, repost mutations
- `ContentView.jsx` -- bookmark, follow, reaction mutations
- `comments.jsx` -- line 156-161, catch block currently does `throw new Error('error adding comments')` -- replace with `toast.error('Failed to post comment. Please try again.')`
